 48	/**
 49	 * The `/admin/content` editor (CMS plan sub-commit C5).
 50	 *
 51	 * It edits the one bilingual `SiteContent` document over three sections —
 52	 * conferences, team, translations — and persists via `Storage`:
 53	 *   - **Save draft** writes `content/site.draft.json` (private to admin);
 54	 *   - **Publish** writes `content/site.json`, removes the draft, and **busts the
 55	 *     `Content` read cache** so the change is live on the next public read with
 56	 *     NO redeploy (D3);
 57	 *   - per-image **Upload** stores the raw bytes under `images/uploads/…` and
 58	 *     rewrites the targeted `…key` field to the new bucket object key (the
 59	 *     resize/WebP/thumbnail pipeline is deferred — CMS plan §"Non-goals").
 60	 *
 61	 * The merge-onto-current-document strategy (`~/lib/content/admin-form`) means the
 62	 * form only carries the fields it renders; every unedited deep field (long bios,
 63	 * `Option` registration windows, image keys) survives, and the merged result is
 64	 * Schema-decoded at the single boundary before it is stored
 65	 * (`boundary-discipline`, `make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`).
